        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>March 28 1851</date></p>
			<p><sic><addressee>Mr. I. Lesser</addressee></sic></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p>As I am residing now here&#44; you<lb/> will in future not send that Book<lb/> to <placeName>Edgefield U. S. C.</placeName> but send<lb/> me my a&#47;c to <placeName>180 &#38; 182 corner Centre &#38; <del>Stret</del><lb/> Hester</placeName>&#44; to <persName>Pecan &#38; Smith</persName>. I will<lb/> send you the money to <placeName>Pha.</placeName> or should<lb/> I come on <sic>their</sic> before you send it<lb/> I will call on you and pay it. I<lb/> remain Very Resp Yours</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author"><hi rend="underline">I. Cohn</hi></persName></p>
			<p>P.S. I bought of you a few years<lb/> ago a new sett of Prayer books<lb/> but my Shabbath book got lost<lb/> it was full bound. If you will send<lb/> one with the Bill you shall recd<lb/> pay in full. If my Year<lb/> of Subscription is out I wish you<lb/> would not send any more</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><hi rend="underline">Paid</hi></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p>Editor of the Occident</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Pa</placeName></p>
          
        </body>
